---
import PageShell from '../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'Overview', level: 2 },
  { id: 'plans-and-coverage', text: 'Plans and Coverage', level: 2 },
  { id: 'pricing', text: 'Pricing', level: 2 },
  { id: 'pros-and-cons', text: 'Pros and Cons', level: 2 },
  { id: 'claims-and-service', text: 'Claims and Service', level: 2 },
  { id: 'who-its-for', text: 'Who It\'s For', level: 2 },
  { id: 'alternatives', text: 'Alternatives to Consider', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Cigna vs Allianz', href: '/compare/cigna-global-vs-allianz-care' },
  { title: 'Cigna vs BUPA', href: '/compare/bupa-global-vs-cigna-global' },
  { title: 'Cigna vs Aetna', href: '/compare/cigna-global-vs-aetna-international' },
  { title: 'Best Expat Insurance', href: '/best/expat-health-insurance' },
  { title: 'Cigna in Spain', href: '/countries/spain/insurance/cigna-global' },
  { title: 'Cigna in Thailand', href: '/countries/thailand/insurance/cigna-global' },
];

const planColumns = [
  { key: 'plan', header: 'Plan' },
  { key: 'coverage', header: 'Coverage' },
  { key: 'deductible', header: 'Deductible Options' },
  { key: 'bestFor', header: 'Best For' },
];

const planRows = [
  { plan: 'Silver', coverage: 'Inpatient + Day Patient', deductible: '$0 - $10,000', bestFor: 'Major medical only' },
  { plan: 'Gold', coverage: 'Silver + Outpatient', deductible: '$0 - $10,000', bestFor: 'Comprehensive care' },
  { plan: 'Platinum', coverage: 'Gold + Enhanced Benefits', deductible: '$0 - $5,000', bestFor: 'Premium coverage' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Cigna Global Review"
  description="In-depth review of Cigna Global international health insurance. Coverage, pricing, pros and cons for expats."
  headline="Cigna Global International Health Insurance Review"
  subheadline="A detailed look at Cigna Global's plans, pricing, and whether they might be right for your expat needs."
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Get a Cigna Global Quote"
  ctaButtonHref="/best/expat-health-insurance"
>
  <h2 id="overview">Overview</h2>
  <p>
    Cigna Global is one of the most recognized names in international health insurance. Part of the Cigna Corporation, they've been providing expat health coverage for decades and serve members in over 200 countries.
  </p>
  <p>
    The company is known for its large provider network, comprehensive coverage options, and strong customer service. They're particularly popular among expat families and corporate assignees.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Quick Facts</h3>
    <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600">
      <li><strong>Headquarters:</strong> Delaware, USA</li>
      <li><strong>Countries Covered:</strong> 200+</li>
      <li><strong>Network Providers:</strong> 1.5 million+</li>
      <li><strong>Plan Types:</strong> Silver, Gold, Platinum</li>
      <li><strong>US Coverage:</strong> Available as add-on</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <CTABox
    title="Get a Personalized Quote"
    description="See what Cigna Global would cost for your situation."
    buttonText="Get Quote"
    buttonHref="/best/expat-health-insurance"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <h2 id="plans-and-coverage">Plans and Coverage</h2>
  <p>
    Cigna Global offers three main plan tiers. Each tier builds on the previous one with additional benefits.
  </p>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={planColumns} rows={planRows} />
  </div>

  <h3>Core Coverage (All Plans)</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Hospital stays and surgery</li>
    <li>Emergency treatment</li>
    <li>Cancer treatment</li>
    <li>Medical evacuation</li>
    <li>Repatriation of remains</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Optional Add-Ons</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Outpatient:</strong> Doctor visits, tests, prescriptions (included in Gold/Platinum)</li>
    <li><strong>International Health and Wellbeing:</strong> Wellness programs and screenings</li>
    <li><strong>Dental:</strong> Preventive and major dental work</li>
    <li><strong>Vision:</strong> Eye exams and glasses/contacts</li>
    <li><strong>Maternity:</strong> Pregnancy and childbirth (10-month waiting period)</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="pricing">Pricing</h2>
  <p>
    Cigna Global pricing depends on your age, plan tier, deductible, and coverage area. Adding US coverage increases premiums significantly.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>Estimated monthly premiums (excluding US):</strong>
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Age 30, Gold plan: $140-200/month</li>
    <li>Age 45, Gold plan: $220-300/month</li>
    <li>Age 55, Gold plan: $350-450/month</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    <strong>Adding US coverage</strong> typically increases premiums by 40-60%.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>Higher deductibles</strong> can reduce premiums by 20-35%. The $5,000 and $10,000 deductible options make the plan more affordable if you're comfortable with higher out-of-pocket costs.
  </p>

  <CTABox
    title="See Your Actual Price"
    description="Get a quote based on your age, location, and coverage needs."
    buttonText="Get a Quote"
    buttonHref="/best/expat-health-insurance"
  />

  <h2 id="pros-and-cons">Pros and Cons</h2>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-green-50 border border-green-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-green-900 mb-3">Pros</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-green-800">
        <li>Large global network with 1.5M+ providers</li>
        <li>Direct billing at many hospitals</li>
        <li>24/7 customer service in multiple languages</li>
        <li>User-friendly online portal and app</li>
        <li>Good maternity and family options</li>
        <li>Established reputation and financial stability</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-red-50 border border-red-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-red-900 mb-3">Cons</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-red-800">
        <li>Premiums can be higher than competitors</li>
        <li>US coverage adds significant cost</li>
        <li>Pre-existing condition exclusions apply</li>
        <li>Maternity has 10-month waiting period</li>
        <li>Some report slow claim reimbursements</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="claims-and-service">Claims and Service</h2>

  <h3>Filing Claims</h3>
  <p>
    Cigna Global offers multiple ways to file claims:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Online portal (recommended)</li>
    <li>Mobile app</li>
    <li>Email</li>
    <li>Mail (paper forms)</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    Claims are typically processed within 5-10 business days. Direct billing with network hospitals means you often don't need to file claims for major procedures.
  </p>

  <h3>Customer Service</h3>
  <p>
    Cigna Global provides 24/7 customer support. You can reach them by phone, email, or through their online portal. Support is available in multiple languages.
  </p>
  <p>
    Customer reviews generally rate their service positively, though some mention occasional delays during peak periods.
  </p>

  <h2 id="who-its-for">Who It's For</h2>
  <p>
    Cigna Global may be a good fit if you:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Want a large, established provider network</li>
    <li>Prefer direct billing over reimbursement</li>
    <li>Have a family and need comprehensive coverage</li>
    <li>Value strong customer service</li>
    <li>Can afford mid-to-premium pricing</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    It may not be ideal if you:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Are on a tight budget</li>
    <li>Don't need extensive provider networks</li>
    <li>Are looking for the lowest possible premiums</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="alternatives">Alternatives to Consider</h2>
  <p>
    If Cigna Global doesn't seem like the right fit, consider these alternatives:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Allianz Care:</strong> Often 10-15% cheaper with good flexibility. <a href="/providers/allianz-care">Read our review</a></li>
    <li><strong>BUPA Global:</strong> Premium option with extensive benefits</li>
    <li><strong>IMG Global:</strong> Budget-friendly with high-deductible options</li>
    <li><strong>Aetna International:</strong> Good choice if you need seamless US coverage</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    <a href="/compare/cigna-global-vs-allianz-care">See our Cigna vs Allianz comparison</a>
  </p>

  <CTABox
    title="Ready to Compare?"
    description="See how Cigna Global compares to other options for your needs."
    buttonText="Compare Plans"
    buttonHref="/best/expat-health-insurance"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This review is for informational purposes only. Plan details, pricing, and availability change. We are not affiliated with Cigna Global and are not insurance brokers. Verify all information directly with Cigna before purchasing.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
